I used to say great things about this restaurant but now they are getting too too greedy and guess over what? Tehina sauce. After trying to get them on the phone for 20 minutes, finally answer the phone placing an order for 3 sandwiches, a platter, and 4 soups. And asking for extra tehina sauce, the guy goes you want 4 little containers of sauce, its half a pound am going to charge you $5. The order I was ready to place would have been at least $130 for a few containers of tehina I ended up canceling the entire order because it's not right this is Jewish and kosher restaurants thinking like they are the only ones who serve food and always make it seem like they are doing you a favor by placing your order. I will not step foot in this store ever.

Food: Amazing! It's fresh and there's that homemade taste! Place: The place is small, but I noticed that many people get takeout, so for a week lunch it was ok. Service: It was great. The lady gave us a good suggestion for the appetizers and brought us a huge pitcher of water. Notes: This is already one of my favorite kosher restaurants in NYC. It reminds me a restaurant called Z Deli, located in São Paulo, Brazil, where I used to go when I lived there. The food in both places tastes so similar, that made me feel a bit nostalgic, even the saltiness was the same. Yes, the food is a bit salty, but I don't mind it once in a while. Actually, all grandma's food seems to be a bit salty. All food is fresh and homemade though!! I'll certainly recommend and return to this place
